      "instruction": "Step 1"
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Heat a large heavy saucepan with a tight-fitting lid over medium heat. Add oil and rice and cook, stirring, until the rice is just beginning to brown, 4 to 5 minutes. Add onion and salt and cook, stirring, until the onion begins to soften, about 2 minutes. Add garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute more. Pour tomato sauce over the rice and cook, stirring, for 1 minute."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Step 2"
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Stir in broth and bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer, cover and cook until the rice is cooked, about 15 minutes. Stir in vegetables and serve."
    },
